  "scopeRestrictions": {
    "linearAttentionLayers": "bound",
    "linearAttentionLayersDetail": "Qwen 3.6 27B is a hybrid architecture (16 full-attention + 48 gated-DeltaNet SSM layers). The smoke config now carries the SSM body sequence with repeat=48: conv1d_depthwise -> l2_normalize(q/k) -> linear_attention. The three body ops route through exec-v1 opToSpec, semantic CSL emit, host-plan compile params/bindings, and reference-interpreter parity. WSE hardware receipts remain R3-2 gated.",
    "mropeInterleaved": "bound",
    "mropeInterleavedDetail": "modelConfig.mropeSection=[11,11,10] is now plumbed through ModelConfig.mrope_section into rope compile params (mrope_t_pairs/mrope_h_pairs/mrope_w_pairs). The host validates T+H+W == num_pairs (32 at headDim=256, partialRotaryFactor=0.25). The kernel-side rope math is mrope-agnostic: cos/sin tables are generated host-side with per-section position multipliers folded in, and the kernel applies them per-pair. For text-only inference the image/video positions are zero so cos=1/sin=0 in those sections; the rotation reduces to standard 1D RoPE for the text section but the wiring is now in place for image/video bring-up.",
    "causalAttentionPrefill": "bound",
    "causalAttentionPrefillDetail": "AttentionScoresBody accepts causal_mode in {.none, .causal, .sliding_window} (emit_kernel_body_attention.zig). The 27B per-PE residency redesign is wired: opToSpec routes `attention_prefill_kv_axis_sharded` to a semantic-ops pattern that delegates to TSIR's emitKvAxisSharded with multi-Q causal-prefill (query_seq_len=8, head_dim=256) and the host plan supplies 2D PE grid + kv_len + slots_per_pe via `attention_prefill_kv_axis_sharded` compile params (csl_host_plan_tool.zig). The smoke config swaps the prefill attention step to `attention_prefill_kv_axis_sharded` so `attn_prefill` no longer tripping `linker_pe_memory_overflow` at manifest shape.",
    "attnPrefillPeMemoryOverflow": "bound",
    "attnPrefillPeMemoryOverflowDetail": "Closed by the kv-axis-sharded multi-Q body. Per-PE working set at width=height=512, query_seq_len=8, head_dim=256: Q stripe ~= 8 KiB, K/V stripe ~= 8 KiB each, partials buffer ~= 8 KiB, attn_scores ~= 32 B → ~= 32 KiB total, comfortably under the WSE-3 48 KiB per-PE budget. Tail slots (gk >= kv_len) are masked to -1e30 so the over-provisioning of PE positions is numerically idempotent.",
    "attentionOutputGate": "bound",
    "attentionOutputGateDetail": "Qwen 3.6 27B applies sigmoid(qGateProjection) * attnOutput before the O projection. The TSIR sigmoid_gated body op, the doe_wgsl classifier surface, and the exec-v1 opToSpec map (with `o_gate` aliased to `sigmoid_gated`) are all wired. The smoke config now declares an explicit `o_gate` step between attention and o_proj that reads (q_proj_output, attention_output) → gated. Receipts surface the gate as a discrete kernel.",
    "swigluFfnFusedGate": "bound",
    "swigluFfnFusedGateDetail": "Qwen FFN is silu(gate_proj(x)) * up_proj(x) → down_proj. The smoke config now declares the activation step as `silu_gated` with inputsFrom=[gate_proj, up_proj]; the TSIR silu_gated body op + classifier + opToSpec + host-plan gated bindings are all wired. Receipts surface the gate as a discrete kernel."
  },
